* I'm launching a YAML Support and Sponsorship Business
  * YAML development, maintenance, support, consulting, training
  * "YES" - YAML Enterprise Sustainability

* I'd like Microsoft to be involved in the future of YAML
  * Keep that in mind during this talk
  * What does Microsoft want for YAML?


----
== YS (YAMLScript)

* `ys` is the YS command line tool

$ vim file1.yaml
$ ys --load --yaml file1.yaml
$ ys -l file1.yaml
$ ys -l file1.yaml | jq
$ ys -Y file1.yaml

$ ys -e 'say: "Hello, $(base64-decode(\"TWljcm9zb2Z0\"))!"'


----
== Dynamic YAML Loaders for All Languages

* YS has YAML Loaders for 15 (and counting) languages
  * Go, Rust, Java, C#, Python, Ruby, NodeJS, etc
* https://yamlscript.org/doc/bindings/#currently-available-libraries
* Same features, bugs, and fixes everywhere!

$ vim file1.py
$ python file1.py
$ vim file2.py
$ python file2.py
$ diff <(python file1.py) <(python file2.py) && echo "No differences!"


----
== Why YS?

* Make YAML Dynamic

* Solve YAML's problems
  * For Everybody, Everywhere, All at Once!

* Loads existing YAML/JSON files as expected
  * YS is 100% valid YAML
  * JSON is 100% valid YAML and YS

* The !ys-v0 tag makes YAML Dynamic


----
== YS is actually a Complete, Functional Programming Language

* Functions, Variables, Conditionals, Loops, Modules, Standard Libraries, etc
* Transpiles to the Clojure Lisp
  * But is native binary, no JVM involved (GraalVM native-image)
  $ ys -e 'say: 42 / 0'
  $ ys -Se 'say: 42 / 0'
* Batteries included
  * 1000+ built-in functions (all clojure.core etc)
  * File I/O, HTTP, Shell, Env Vars, JSON, YAML, etc
* Soon to work with as Go Lang via Glojure
  * Compile YAML to Go code or binaries
  * Compile to WebAssembly (browser and server)
* YS Code is surprisingly concise and readable
  * https://gist.github.com/ingydotnet/90ab729fad4c5518b38f98eda097021c
* Great for scripting and automations
  * Most of the yamlscript repo automations are written in YS
  * https://github.com/yaml/yamlscript/blob/v0/util/release-yamlscript


