----
== YS Empowers DevOps Engineers

* People who write DevOps configs need programming features
* YAML doesn't have that
* Need to use other tools like Jinja2, Helm, Kustomize, etc
* YS gives them those features in YAML itself


----
== Scripting with YS

$ vim 99-bottles.ys
$ ys 99-bottles.ys
$ ys 99-bottles.ys 3

* -x Trace Debugging (like bash -x)
$ ys -x 99-bottles.ys


----
== Compile YS to a Go binary

$ rm -fr 99-bottles
$ (cd ./soon && util/ysj --to=go -o ../99-bottles ../99-bottles.ys)
$ ./99-bottles 3

$ rm -f 99-bottles
$ (cd ./soon && util/ysj --to=go -o ../99-bottles/ ../99-bottles.ys)
$ vim 99-bottles/
$ ./99-bottles/99-bottles 3


----
== Useful YS scripts

* yamllm - A CLI for LLMs
  $ yamllm 'Will YAMLScript be adopted by Microsoft?'
  * https://github.com/yaml/yamllm/blob/main/bin/yamllm

* Creating GitHub Gists
  $ vim $(which gist)
  $ gist $(which gist)


----
== What's Next for YAML?

* So many great ideas for improving YAML

* SchemaYS - A YAML Schema Language
  * Like JSON Schema, but better
  * Written in YS

* Fundamental YS Functions for go-yaml
  * !load, !merge, !concat, !if, !map, !filter, !reduce, etc
  * Opt-in of course

* New YAML Spec Version 1.3 or 2.0
  * Fix spec ambiguities and errors
  * Add new features based on YS experience
  * Support feature extensions


----
== Is Moving YAML Forward even Possible?

* Can we actually improve YAML?
* New spec version 1.3 or 2.0?
* Specs need to be implemented!
* The YAML spec is incredibly hard to implement
* YAML test suite
  * https://matrix.yaml.info


----
== The Solution

* What if there was a new YAML framework?
* That worked the same everywhere?
* Full featured
* Highly configurable
* Shipped to every modern programming language

* When 1.3 is published it's already implemented
  * Even before a new spec is finalized!

* Coming very soon...
  * Essentially a slight rework of YS


